The 'Final Upsert' logic in applyOp for UPDATE_ITEM only handles object wrappers. If the parentContainer is a CRDT array wrapper, the update will be ignored. This means updateItem cannot be used to append to an array by index if the index doesn't exist. While addItem is the preferred way to add to arrays, updateItem should ideally behave consistently across types or explicitly handle array upserts.
